---
import InfoLayout from '../layouts/InfoLayout.astro';
---

<InfoLayout
  title="Terms of Service · StudentLancers"
  description="The terms and conditions for using StudentLancers."
  eyebrow="Legal"
  heading="Terms of Service"
  lead="Last updated: June 5, 2026. These terms cover the use of studentlancers.com and any related services."
>
  <h2>1. Eligibility</h2>
  <p>
    You must be at least 18 years old to use StudentLancers. Students must
    verify a current .edu email address. Companies must verify a business
    email address and agree to fund engagements through our escrow system.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Accounts</h2>
  <p>
    You are responsible for keeping your account credentials secure. We are
    not liable for losses caused by unauthorized access to your account.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Fees</h2>
  <p>
    StudentLancers charges an 8% platform fee on completed engagements.
    Payment-processing fees are passed through at cost. There are no setup
    fees, monthly fees, or cancellation fees.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Work product & IP</h2>
  <p>
    Once an engagement is approved and the student is paid, the company
    receives a license to the deliverables as described in the brief. Until
    approval, the work remains the student's.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Disputes</h2>
  <p>
    If a company and student cannot agree on whether a deliverable meets
    the brief, our support team mediates. Decisions are made within four
    business hours during business days.
  </p>

  <h2>6. Conduct</h2>
  <p>
    We do not tolerate harassment, discrimination, or fraud. We may suspend
    or terminate accounts that violate these terms. See our
    <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for how we handle your data.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Changes</h2>
  <p>
    We may update these terms. Significant changes are announced by email
    and on this page at least 14 days before they take effect.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    Questions? <a href="/contact">Get in touch</a>. We answer within one
    business day.
  </p>
</InfoLayout>
